level.heading:
RETAIL ESTABLISHMENTS SUBJECT TO CARRYOUT BAG REQUIREMENTS (§ 21-1003)
    For the purposes of this chapter, the term “retail establishment” means:

      (a)
      Any business required to have a Public Health: Food Establishment Retailndorsement to a basic business license pursuant to D.C. Official Code §7-2827; and


      (b)
      Any business required to have an off-premises retailer’s license, class Ar B, pursuant to D.C. Official Code § 25-112.

    Such retail establishments include, but are not limited to, the following typesf business:
    Bakeries;
    Delicatessens;
    Grocery stores;
    Convenience stores that sell food;
    Restaurants (subject to the exception set forth in section 1006);
    Food vendors;
    Street vendors that sell food;
    Liquor stores; and
    Any business that sells food items, whether or not the principal purpose of theusiness is to sell food items, including a department store or electronicstore that has a Public Health: Food Establishment Retail endorsement to itsasic business license.
    Source: Final Rulemaking published at 57 DCR 7208, 7210 (August 13, 2010).
